  "text": "Based on these superior qualities of MAPC, we aimed to assess the anti-inflammatory and neuroprotective potential of MAPC cells in the preterm brain exposed to global HI. We hypothesized that systemic administration of MAPC cells would attenuate cerebral and peripheral inflammation and prevent structural and functional brain injury after global HI in the preterm ovine fetus. We tested our hypothesis in a well-established preclinical animal model of preterm global HI. In this model, preterm ovine fetuses were exposed to global HI by transient umbilical cord occlusion (UCO) at 0.7 gestation which is equivalent to 30-32 weeks human gestation [CITATION_1] followed by systemic administration of MAPC therapy during a 7-day reperfusion period.",
